1
00:01:31,370 --> 00:01:34,940
[Unbreakable Ⅱ]

2
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:37,900
[Episode 3]

3
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:40,560
Sir, please carry it upstairs for me.

4
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,039
I really can't carry it.

5
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,430
Besides, the seller promised

6
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,200
it would be delivered to our door.

7
00:01:46,220 --> 00:01:47,350
This is second-hand,

8
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:48,580
and it's not an official delivery.

9
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:49,990
Besides, I'm just the driver.

10
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,050
I'm already being kind enough by delivering it downstairs.

11
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:54,280
If you want me to deliver it upstairs, well...

12
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:54,810
Right?

13
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:57,070
Alright, alright. How much do you want?

14
00:01:57,270 --> 00:01:57,789
50.

15
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,200
30.

16
00:01:59,229 --> 00:02:00,230
40 at the lowest.

17
00:02:00,450 --> 00:02:01,680
30 is the most I can do.

18
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:02,560
It's pretty heavy. 40.

19
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,350
Luo Yingzi?

20
00:02:03,370 --> 00:02:04,440
What are you doing?

21
00:02:04,550 --> 00:02:06,430
You came just in time. You saved me 30 yuan.

22
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:08,120
Sir, I don't need your help anymore. Thank you.

23
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:10,280
Here, help me carry this cabinet upstairs.

24
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:10,750
Come on.

25
00:02:10,770 --> 00:02:11,700
Wait a minute.

26
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,430
So, the office you mentioned is your house?

27
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:16,670
Time was limited.

28
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:18,300
I really couldn't find a place to rent.

29
00:02:18,530 --> 00:02:20,440
At home, Xia Shu and I have already tidied everything up.

30
00:02:20,460 --> 00:02:21,800
Check it out; it's nice.

31
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:23,150
Mr. Dong said

32
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:24,329
he was coming for an inspection this afternoon.

33
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,450
You're letting him inspect your house?

34
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:28,170
Do you think Mr. Dong is that easy to fool?

35
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,280
Just go up and take a look first.

36
00:02:30,470 --> 00:02:31,770
If it's really not okay for you,

37
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,150
we can arrange to meet him at a cafe, okay?

38
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:34,710
Let's go.

39
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,000
Come on.

40
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,360
You are such...

41
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:38,840
Come on. One, two, three. There you go.

42
00:02:39,170 --> 00:02:40,120
Hold steady.

43
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:43,340
You're not carrying it?

44
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:45,950
I need to keep an eye on this cabinet.

45
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,260
Who would want this old cabinet?

46
00:02:48,290 --> 00:02:49,120
You have no idea.

47
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:51,190
Right before the Spring Festival, you can see all sorts of people.

48
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:52,650
What if someone steals the cabinet?

49
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,520
So you're making me carry it all by myself?

50
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:56,270
Just do it.

51
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,140
After you're done, come back down and find me.

52
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,520
Your cabinet is shorter than mine.

53
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:03,520
I can carry mine. Why can't you carry yours?

54
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:06,000
There must be something inside.

55
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,630
Be careful on the stairs.

56
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,120
Don't bump the cabinet's legs.

57
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,440
Why didn't you ask me earlier?

58
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:13,000
I could have just paid the man.

59
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,870
Why didn't you come earlier? I spent a lot of time haggling with him.

60
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:16,360
I'm wearing a dress.

61
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:18,630
-And now I have to help you carry the cabinet.
-Qiu Hua, what did you just say?

62
00:03:18,650 --> 00:03:19,490
What?

63
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,050
This is a residential area,

64
00:03:21,079 --> 00:03:22,870
not a place for you to run your business.

65
00:03:22,890 --> 00:03:24,170
So what?

66
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,280
This is our own home.

67
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,470
We can do whatever we want here.

68
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,710
We can accept you running other businesses,

69
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,960
but you're opening a law firm here.

70
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,280
What kind of people come to a law firm?

71
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,200
Yeah, what kind of people come to a law firm?

72
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:33,840
Murderers, rapists,

73
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:34,720
pimps—

74
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,079
all sorts of messed-up people.

75
00:03:36,310 --> 00:03:38,100
How can others feel safe here?

76
00:03:38,170 --> 00:03:39,450
Running a law firm at home—

77
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,440
won't the clients distrust us?

78
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:45,329
It's fine. Check it out later. It's quite nice inside.

79
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:48,130
Anyway, let's just get them to come first.

80
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,590
Right. We can't let them do it.

81
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,630
If they insist,

82
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:56,940
let's report them to the police station.

83
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,160
What's going on?

84
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,560
You came back at the right time. I was just about to find you.

85
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:02,680
I just want to ask you something.

86
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:03,710
This is a residential area.

87
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,590
How can you open a law firm here?

88
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:06,240
I'm sorry.

89
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:06,960
Xia Shu,

90
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,030
help me move the cabinet.

91
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,910
I'm not running a law firm here.

92
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:12,910
Look at that signboard.

93
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:14,620
It's hanging right there, obviously.

94
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:16,120
Gosh.

95
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,620
Sorry for the misunderstanding.

96
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,390
Here's the thing.

97
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:20,430
I am going to open a law firm,

98
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,000
but not here.

99
00:04:22,180 --> 00:04:24,740
It's going to be in that office building right in front.

100
00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:26,710
This assistant was just hired.

101
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:28,160
She's young and knows nothing.

102
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:30,190
I told her to hang the signboard outside,

103
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,920
and she thought I meant to hang it outside my home.

104
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:32,950
How could that be?

105
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,070
It has to be at the door of my law firm, right?

106
00:04:35,110 --> 00:04:36,930
Sorry for the misunderstanding.

107
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:37,950
I'll take it down right now.

108
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:38,560
Take it down now.

109
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:38,950
Okay, okay.

110
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:40,270
Okay, I will.

111
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:40,950
What a false alarm.

112
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:41,890
It must be taken down.

113
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,870
We should get along in peace.

114
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:44,600
Yes, you're right.

115
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:46,260
Thank you for understanding.

116
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,800
I'm sorry.

117
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,200
I really didn't know.

118
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:56,240
I thought hanging it up early would help attract clients.

119
00:04:56,450 --> 00:04:58,490
Are you out of your mind?

120
00:04:58,670 --> 00:05:00,040
This is a residential building.

121
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,970
You hung such a big signboard at the door.

122
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,240
Of course they wanted to kick us out.

123
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,550
Stop making things worse for me, alright?

124
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:09,440
Xia Shu, you're not suited for our firm.

125
00:05:10,890 --> 00:05:12,770
Our firm is too small

126
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:14,410
to afford someone like you.

127
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:16,750
You should go somewhere else.

128
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:18,800
Qiu Hua. Qiu Hua.

129
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,750
Well... Qiu Hua.

130
00:05:19,780 --> 00:05:21,250
Didn't she cause us enough trouble?

131
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:23,150
She's not someone who is legally incompetent.

132
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,250
Besides, if it weren't for her,

133
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,750
would Xu Jianshe's case

134
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:27,920
have ended up like that?

135
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:30,300
Could Liangcheng Law Firm have kicked the three of us out?

136
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,520
We can barely manage ourselves right now.

137
00:05:34,930 --> 00:05:35,690
We simply don't have the capacity

138
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,180
to take care of a young lady like her.

139
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:38,720
Xia Shu,

140
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:39,550
you,

141
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:40,420
please leave.

142
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:42,950
I hope you find a new place to work soon.

143
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,510
Luo.

144
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:46,390
Qiu Hua,

145
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:48,590
today, this was also my fault.

146
00:05:48,610 --> 00:05:49,720
I didn't remind her.

147
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,680
Please calm down.

148
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,000
Qiu,

149
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,530
I know I was wrong.

150
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,790
I really do.

151
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,620
I will definitely make changes in the future.

152
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,360
Some things can be changed,

153
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:08,500
but some things can never be changed.

154
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,330
Please.

155
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,070
Qiu...

156
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,190
Xia Shu!

157
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:17,520
What did I tell you?

158
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,240
I asked you to get the car.

159
00:06:21,730 --> 00:06:22,940
How's it going?

160
00:06:23,790 --> 00:06:25,430
I had an agreement

161
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:27,090
with Qiu Hua before

162
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,800
that we can only keep you here

163
00:06:28,830 --> 00:06:30,830
if you can get the car back.

164
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:34,020
Have you gotten it back?

165
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,610
Not yet.

166
00:06:35,690 --> 00:06:38,460
Then what are you waiting for? Go get it.

167
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:40,320
But...

168
00:06:40,350 --> 00:06:42,350
But what? Go!

169
00:06:42,370 --> 00:06:43,770
Okay, okay.

170
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:48,430
I'm so pissed.

171
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,680
Luo.

172
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:59,450
Could you lend me some money?

173
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,770
I don't have money for a taxi.

174
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,370
Where's your money?

175
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:06,270
Didn't you say last night

176
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:08,000
that there was 5,000 in your account?

177
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,950
I have a personal credit card.

178
00:07:10,650 --> 00:07:12,460
Today's the payment due date.

179
00:07:12,930 --> 00:07:14,720
As soon as I woke up this morning, the money was deducted.

180
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,200
You can go on foot.

181
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,560
It's too far.

182
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:22,560
Fine, just leave.

183
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,240
I'll give you 10 yuan on WeChat later,

184
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:25,950
so you can take the bus.

185
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,070
Okay.

186
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,690
Which bus should I take?

187
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,240
Take whatever you want.

188
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:34,060
Look it up yourself.

189
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,750
Seriously.

190
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,930
Young people's logic...

191
00:07:43,450 --> 00:07:45,300
Luo Yingzi, stop acting with me.

192
00:07:45,909 --> 00:07:47,180
You're just trying to mediate.

193
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,690
You're being a peacemaker.

194
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:50,990
Qiu Hua, calm down.

195
00:07:51,290 --> 00:07:53,680
Don't get mad because of Xia Shu.

196
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,159
You know I'm soft-hearted.

197
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:57,390
When others beg me, I...

198
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:59,060
How about this?

199
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,730
How about I hire her as my assistant

200
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,500
with my own money,

201
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,790
so it'll have nothing to do with our law firm? Is that okay?

202
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:09,090
The problem is, I promised her before

203
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:11,100
that as long as she gets the car back, I'll keep her.

204
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:14,060
I can only kick her out if she doesn't get it back.

205
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:15,560
She's doing it now, right?

206
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:16,870
So I can't really say anything.

207
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,780
Are we really going to work here?

208
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,380
As long as we work hard,

209
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:27,050
there'll be bread and milk.

210
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,840
Everything is hard at the beginning.

211
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:31,720
See? It's...

212
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:34,039
I've been looking at it for a while.

213
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,080
Yeah, isn't this...

214
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,549
a pretty good start?

215
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:41,880
Forget it.

216
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:45,250
Let's meet Mr. Dong at a cafe.

217
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:53,340
Stop pushing.

218
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:03,600
I'm getting off here. Excuse me.

219
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:14,930
Don't go!

220
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:17,070
My purse!

221
00:09:17,570 --> 00:09:18,410
Don't go!

222
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,560
My purse! My purse!

223
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,630
Stop!

224
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:36,030
Why are you here again?

225
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,510
Director Zhang said he doesn't know you

226
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,730
and told me not to let you in.

227
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:40,790
Sir,

228
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,830
could you please make another call for me?

229
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,790
I was just

230
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,360
talking to him here a few days ago.

231
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,150
How could he not know me now?

232
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,240
No, Miss.

233
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,290
Please don't make this difficult for me, alright?

234
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:49,870
Please leave.

235
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,030
Stop! Stop!

236
00:09:57,980 --> 00:09:59,700
I told you you're not allowed in. Why are you trying to barge in?

237
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,890
Sir, I'm begging you.

238
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:02,310
Please contact him again for me.

239
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,750
If I can't see him today,

240
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:05,130
I don't even know where I'm going to eat.

241
00:10:05,210 --> 00:10:06,200
Don't you have his number?

242
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,630
Contact him yourself. Just go.

243
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:08,260
Leave.

244
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:09,840
I called him, but he didn't answer.

245
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,030
Then what's there to say?

246
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,270
Just go. Leave.

247
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:14,270
Stay away from the gate. They'll get off work soon.

248
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:15,150
There'll be many cars coming out.

249
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:16,830
You can't tell me what to do out here.

250
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:25,750
Why didn't we hear anything at all,

251
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:27,360
and you guys just got fired by Liangcheng?

252
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:28,390
Why?

253
00:10:29,530 --> 00:10:30,250
Mr. Dong,

254
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:33,300
you've been in business for so long.

255
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:34,830
Can't you see?

256
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,790
This past year, Ms. Qiu and I

257
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:37,850
have been progressing

258
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,710
really fast in our work.

259
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:42,120
Especially with your patent case.

260
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:44,050
Before us,

261
00:10:44,190 --> 00:10:45,560
had Liangcheng Law Firm ever handled

262
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,910
such a complicated patent case? Right?

263
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,190
I guess it's just the jealousy that comes with success.

264
00:10:51,370 --> 00:10:52,590
That's the only way to see it.

265
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:56,250
Yes, when they told me about it,

266
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:59,150
I said patent cases require

267
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:02,100
much more specialization than other cases.

268
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:03,790
Your firm...

269
00:11:04,660 --> 00:11:06,300
No, I should say "their firm."

270
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:07,120
Right?

271
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:08,000
Right.

272
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,720
I honestly haven't seen anyone else in their firm

273
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:12,550
who could handle such cases,

274
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,390
except for the two of you.

275
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:16,520
We really appreciate

276
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,120
your recognition of us.

277
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,600
But Mr Dong,

278
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:22,510
we didn't have a fallout with Liangcheng Law Firm.

279
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:24,410
-We weren't fired.
-Yes.

280
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:25,750
Should I say it?

281
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,570
Go ahead.

282
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:28,600
Okay.

283
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,430
Actually, Qiu Hua and I

284
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:32,580
have always wanted to start our own business.

285
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:35,050
And I'm quite frank.

286
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,790
One time, I got too excited and accidentally let it slip.

287
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,840
After Fang Lihong found out, she felt very sorry about it.

288
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,010
She tried every possible way to keep us,

289
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,720
even saying she would nominate us both as general partners.

290
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:49,670
But since I already said it,

291
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:51,960
if I stayed on as a partner,

292
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:54,440
wouldn't it seem like

293
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,150
we were threatening them?

294
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:57,550
So,

295
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:01,000
we left resolutely.

296
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,550
But before we left,

297
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,840
Fang Lihong kept us talking for a long time.

298
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:09,720
Ms. Fang is really willing to help younger lawyers.

299
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:12,040
She really gave us a lot of insightful advice

300
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:15,550
for our future development.

301
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,000
I must say,

302
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,080
it was incredibly enlightening.

303
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,670
What about you, Qiu Hua?

304
00:12:20,690 --> 00:12:22,450
Did you feel the same way after hearing it?

305
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:25,550
That's right, it was truly enlightening.

306
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:26,810
Really eye-opening.

307
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:27,980
Ms. Fang

308
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:29,950
also gave us a few suggestions.

309
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,000
One of the suggestions

310
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:34,390
was that we should

311
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:36,320
focus our business

312
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:39,360
on intellectual property,

313
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:41,670
making patent services

314
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,840
our Yinghua Law Firm's specialty

315
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:45,780
and main business.

316
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:48,640
Qiu Hua and I found it really made sense.

317
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,450
It's like when you go to a doctor.

318
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:53,150
If they claim they can cure everything,

319
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,440
can they really be a good doctor?

320
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:55,980
So, we've decided

321
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:59,080
to specialize in intellectual property going forward.

322
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,390
We've said a lot.

323
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:04,700
Well, Mr. Dong, you see,

324
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,550
we've been handling

325
00:13:06,710 --> 00:13:08,830
your company's cases for a year now.

326
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,320
How about we keep doing it?

327
00:13:13,090 --> 00:13:14,450
We can sign another contract,

328
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,760
and you just need to cancel the one

329
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:17,970
with Liangcheng Law Firm.

330
00:13:18,020 --> 00:13:19,380
I do want to give this business

331
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,210
to you to handle,

332
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,800
but I have to consider

333
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:25,350
your firm's current capabilities

334
00:13:25,490 --> 00:13:26,580
and other aspects.

335
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,880
After all, your firm is newly established.

336
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:33,770
But what does a law firm's strength really depend on?

337
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:35,520
Isn't it about the lawyers?

338
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:38,260
We've already been working together for a year.

339
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:41,430
Both of us have been personally evaluated by you.

340
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,790
It's been a year.

341
00:13:42,810 --> 00:13:44,290
Do you still not trust us?

342
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,500
You really lack confidence

343
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,950
in your ability to judge people.

344
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,690
Yingzi.

345
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:53,120
Mr. Dong didn't mean it.

346
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:55,590
What he means is that he cares about

347
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:57,560
our relationship with Liangcheng Law Firm.

348
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,680
You're really far-sighted.

349
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,950
But if you no longer entrust the cases to them,

350
00:14:02,970 --> 00:14:05,180
you won't have any ties with Liangcheng Law Firm.

351
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:06,490
Has there ever been a case

352
00:14:06,790 --> 00:14:09,390
where the client is afraid of their lawyer?

353
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:11,720
I'm here.

354
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,390
The car's parked at the usual place.

355
00:14:14,110 --> 00:14:15,800
Hurry up, let's go eat.

356
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:18,490
So, he gave my car to his new girlfriend to drive?

357
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,600
Honey!

358
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:22,840
I'm here.

359
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,600
What took you so long?

360
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,750
My boss is always looking for me.

361
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:28,200
Just now, he asked me to stay late.

362
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:29,700
But as soon as I got your call,

363
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,840
I lost my mind.

364
00:14:30,890 --> 00:14:32,890
I made an excuse and slipped out immediately.

365
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,360
But let me make it clear first.

366
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:35,540
If this affects my future,

367
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:37,570
your parents can't blame me for being useless.

368
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:38,360
Shameless.

369
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:39,630
I really don't take you,

370
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:41,230
a little employee, seriously.

371
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:42,360
But

372
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:44,020
if we get married in the future,

373
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:45,880
I won't be able to stand you being so busy every day.

374
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:46,840
Fine.

375
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:49,910
"Nights for a couple are always short, and they got up late.

376
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,330
From then on, the emperor never attended the morning court."

377
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,690
Come on. You call yourself an emperor?

378
00:14:53,890 --> 00:14:55,250
Let's go. What are we going to eat?

379
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:57,520
How about some grilled skewers?

380
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:58,360
There's a place next door.

381
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,480
The taste is pretty good.

382
00:14:59,890 --> 00:15:02,440
You must be used to going there with your ex-girlfriend, right?

383
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:03,550
No.

384
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:05,590
Your ex-girlfriend is pretty weird.

385
00:15:05,620 --> 00:15:08,290
Isn't she the daughter of a high-ranking official? How could she have such low taste?

386
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:09,520
Squatting on the ground every day,

387
00:15:09,540 --> 00:15:11,610
eating grilled skewers with a bunch of roughneck guys.

388
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,270
She's not the daughter of a high-ranking official.

389
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:16,390
Her dad came from

390
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:17,060
a rural production team.

391
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:18,850
As soon as he was no longer a poor farmer,

392
00:15:18,870 --> 00:15:20,150
he had a daughter

393
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,470
who acts like an idiot.

394
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:22,620
Alright, let's go. Let's go to...

395
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,610
Zhang Xiaoguang!

396
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:24,550
Wait a minute.

397
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:26,230
Alright. Hurry up and get in the car.

398
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:26,800
It's alright.

399
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:29,580
It's alright. It's alright.

400
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:30,540
She's just a lunatic.

401
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:31,800
Zhang Xiaoguang, who are you talking about?

402
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:32,900
I'm a lunatic?

403
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:34,440
Wasn't it you who chased after me

404
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,320
relentlessly back then?

405
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:36,420
Who chased after you?

406
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,390
We have nothing to do with each other now.

407
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,890
Please have some self-respect and stop bothering me.

408
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,390
That's her?

409
00:15:43,660 --> 00:15:46,370
Xiaoguang, your taste wasn't that great back then.

410
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:47,870
Get in. Let's go.

411
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:50,960
